## THE GAME — ONE SENTENCE

A seamless first-person medieval fantasy voxel RPG where the player is simultaneously
a hero exploring dungeons, a general commanding squads, and a lord managing a kingdom —
with no loading screens or mode switches between those layers.

---

## CORE DESIGN PILLARS

1. **The Hero** — First-person exploration, direct physical combat (Mount & Blade feel),
   dungeon crawling. The human-scale layer.

2. **The General** — Commanding squads of 10–30 units in field battles. Player can
   fight on the front line OR pull back to issue commands. The skirmish layer.

3. **The Lord** — Overworld strategic map, settlement management, faction politics,
   diplomacy. The kingdom layer.

4. **The Builder** — Free-form voxel construction. Fortifications, homes,
   infrastructure. The world is persistent and reshapable.

These are NOT separate modes. The player flows between all four organically in a
single continuous session.

