## WORLD STRUCTURE

### Two-Layer World
1. **Overworld strategic map** — top-down view of the realm showing kingdoms,
   settlements, roads, armies. Time moves faster here.
2. **Zoomed-in voxel world** — full 3D ground-level gameplay. Where all first-person
   action happens. Contains surface AND underground dungeon layers.

### World Generation
- **Hybrid:** Hand-crafted skeleton (major landmarks, story locations, capitals are
  authored) + proc-gen fills biomes, terrain variation, dungeon layouts, resources
- World seed system for shareable/repeatable worlds
- Terrain is fully persistent — player modifications survive session

### Biomes (current demo map — 40×40 units, 4 quadrants)
- **Meadow** (NW) — open grass fields, wildflowers, a few scattered trees
- **Forest** (NE) — dense voxel trees, dappled light, leaf litter
- **Rocky Hills** (SW) — elevated terrain, large boulders, sparse vegetation
- **Pond** (SE) — depressed basin with water, shoreline trees

### Biomes (planned full game)
- Temperate highlands (starting region)
- Dense ancient forest
- Badlands / war-scarred terrain
- Coastal cliffs
- Mountain range

