## GAMEPLAY SYSTEMS — FULL SCOPE

### Personal Combat
- First-person, direct and physical
- Directional blocking — stance matters
- Weapon weight affects swing speed and stamina drain
- Mounted combat supported
- Magic usable in combat (not a separate mode)
- Death has real consequence (exact mechanic TBD — flag for design decision)

### Army Combat
- Squads of 10–30 units per side
- Player can fight alongside troops in first-person
- OR hold commander key to pull camera up to tactical view (real-time continues below)
- Unit types: infantry, archers, cavalry, mage support
- Terrain matters — voxel hills, walls, and chokepoints are tactical
- Morale system — routing, fear effects

### Settlement System
- Settlement tiers: camp → village → town → city → fortress
- Free-form voxel construction
- NPC role assignment: farmer, soldier, blacksmith, trader
- Supply chains between settlements
- Happiness/unrest system
- Enemy armies can besiege and damage structures

### Factions
- Multiple autonomous competing kingdoms on overworld
- They expand, war, and fall without player involvement
- Player can: be independent / join a faction / found own faction
- Reputation system — persistent, earned through actions

### RPG Progression
- Skill trees: Combat, Magic, Leadership, Crafting, Stealth
- Skills improve through use (swing more → get better)
- No class lock — hybrid builds valid
- Leadership skills directly affect army effectiveness

### Magic
- Learned through gameplay (tomes, teachers, dungeon finds)
- Costly — stamina, health, or resource drain
- Schools: Elemental, Ward, Arcane, Necromantic (forbidden)
- Never trivializes combat

### Dungeons
- Every surface region has underground dungeon layer
- Proc-gen layouts with hand-authored bosses and set pieces
- Multi-floor: surface cave → deep ruins → ancient vaults
- Voxel walls mineable — secrets hidden in geometry
- Rewards: rare materials, unique weapons, spell unlocks, lore

### Narrative
- Sandbox-first — world runs and is interesting without story triggers
- Optional main quest: ancient threat from the dungeon layer
- Threat grows over time if ignored but does not force an ending
- No win condition — world continues indefinitely

